   942→## Part 5: Common Patterns & Anti-Patterns
   943→
   944→### 5.1 Best Practices (GOOD)
   945→
   946→| Pattern | Description | Example |
   947→|---------|-------------|---------|
   948→| **Layered Shadows** | Multiple shadows create realistic depth | `0px 1px 2px`, `0px 4px 8px`, `0px 12px 24px` |
   949→| **Color-Matched Shadows** | Shadows match background hue, not pure black | Use `hsl()` shadows matching theme |
   950→| **Consistent Light Source** | Light from same direction across all elements | Light from top-left 45° angle |
   951→| **Proportional Scaling** | Shadow blur scales with elevation | As offset increases, blur increases |
   952→| **Reduced Motion Respect** | Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` preference | Remove animations for accessibility |
   953→| **Contrast Verification** | WCAG AA/AAA minimum over glass effects | 4.5:1 text contrast minimum |
   954→| **Hardware Acceleration** | Use `will-change: transform` for performance | Enable GPU rendering for smooth animations |
   955→
   956→### 5.2 Anti-Patterns (AVOID)
   957→
   958→| Anti-Pattern | Problem | Solution |
   959→|--------------|---------|----------|
   960→| **Single Heavy Shadow** | Looks flat, lacks sophistication | Use layered shadows instead |
   961→| **Black Shadows Only** | Desaturates background colors | Match shadow to theme colors |
   962→| **No Light Source** | Shadows appear random, confusing | Establish consistent light direction |
   963→| **Over-Blurred Glass** | Reduces readability, poor UX | Keep blur to 10-20px max |
   964→| **Ignoring Reduced Motion** | Accessibility violation, can cause issues | Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion` |
   965→| **Excessive Morphism** | Neumorphism/glassmorphism overuse = confusing | Use strategically, not on every element |
   966→| **Mobile-Unfriendly Blur** | Performance issues on mobile devices | Reduce backdrop-filter on small screens |
   967→| **Low Contrast Text** | WCAG violation, hard to read | Verify contrast ratios for all text |
   968→| **Ignoring Battery State** | Excessive motion drains mobile battery | Provide performance mode (lower animation quality) |
