   128→### @theme vs @theme inline
   129→
   130→**Critical distinction:**
   131→
   132→```css
   133→/* @theme - Value references CSS variable */
   134→@theme {
   135→  --color-primary: #3b82f6;
   136→}
   137→/* Generates: */
   138→.bg-primary {
   139→  background-color: var(--color-primary);
   140→}
   141→
   142→/* @theme inline - Value inlined directly */
   143→@theme inline {
   144→  --color-primary: #3b82f6;
   145→}
   146→/* Generates: */
   147→.bg-primary {
   148→  background-color: #3b82f6;
   149→}
   150→```
   151→
   152→**When to use each:**
   153→
   154→```css
   155→/* Use @theme for runtime overridable values */
   156→@theme {
   157→  --color-brand: oklch(0.57 0.24 276);
   158→}
   159→
   160→:root {
   161→  --color-brand: oklch(0.57 0.24 276);
   162→}
   163→
