content.text:
Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive analysis document:

## Comprehensive CSS Architecture Analysis: Socialaize Styles Directory

### File Structure Overview

```
src/styles/
├── global.css           (528 lines) - Main entry point, layer orchestration, @theme
├── design-system.css    (1337 lines) - Design tokens, color palette, spacing system
├── utilities.css        (840 lines) - Utility classes for glass morphism, focus, accessibility
├── typography.css       (89 lines) - Landing page typography utilities
```

**Total:** 2,794 lines of CSS across 4 files

---

## 1. CSS Architecture & Layering System

### Cascade Layer Organization (global.css:4)

```css
@layer reset, theme, composition, utilities, components, overrides;

@import "./design-system.css" layer(theme);
@import "./typography.css" layer(components);
@import "./utilities.css" layer(utilities);
```

**Why this matters:**
- Explicit layer ordering prevents CSS cascade conflicts
- `theme` layer (design-system.css) sets base tokens
- `components` layer (typography.css) defines component base styles
- `utilities` layer (utilities.css) provides high-level patterns
- Each layer has predictable specificity

**Design Decision:** Tailwind v4 CSS-first approach eliminates bloated config files. All customization flows through CSS custom properties.

---

## 2. Design Token System

### Color Palette Architecture (design-system.css:9-143)

**OKLCH with RGB Fallbacks Pattern:**

```css
:root {
  /* Primary Brand Colors - OKLCH with RGB fallbacks for Safari < 15.4 */
  --color-primary-50: #e6f3f4;                    /* RGB fallback */
  --color-primary-50: oklch(95% 0.03 200);        /* Modern OKLCH */
  --color-primary-100: #cce5e7;
  --color-primary-100: oklch(90% 0.05 200);
  /* ... continues for 50-950 scale */
  --color-primary-500: #007c89;  /* Base teal - brand color */
  --color-primary-500: oklch(50% 0.16 200);
}
```

**Why OKLCH?**
- Perceptually uniform color scales (uniform lightness across all hues)
- Better interpolation between colors
- Modern color space for progressive enhancement
- Safari fallback ensures cross-browser compatibility

**Color Scales:** Each semantic color (primary, success, warning, error, info) has 11 shades (50-950)

**Semantic Color System:**
```css
--color-primary-*      /* Teal #007c89 - Brand color */
--color-success-*      /* Green #10b981 - Positive states */
--color-warning-*      /* Amber #f59e0b - Cautionary states */
--color-error-*        /* Red #ef4444 - Destructive states */
--color-info-*         /* Blue #3b82f6 - Informational states */
--color-gray-*         /* Neutral grays */

/* Surface colors - Adapt with dark mode */
--color-surface-primary        /* #ffffff light, gray-800 dark */
--color-surface-secondary      /* gray-50 light, gray-900 dark */
--color-surface-tertiary       /* gray-100 light, gray-950 dark */
--color-surface-inverse        /* gray-900 light, #ffffff dark */

/* Text colors - Hierarchy system */
--color-text-primary           /* gray-900 light, gray-100 dark */
--color-text-secondary         /* gray-600 light, gray-300 dark */
--color-text-tertiary          /* gray-500 light, gray-400 dark */
--color-text-placeholder       /* gray-400 light, gray-500 dark */
```

### Spacing System (design-system.css:179-217)

**Fixed Spacing Scale (4px base unit):**
```css
--spacing-0: 0;
--spacing-px: 1px;
--spacing-0_5: 0.125rem;   /* 2px */
--spacing-1: 0.25rem;      /* 4px */
--spacing-2: 0.5rem;       /* 8px */
--spacing-3: 0.75rem;      /* 12px */
--spacing-4: 1rem;         /* 16px base */
--spacing-6: 1.5rem;       /* 24px */
--spacing-8: 2rem;         /* 32px */
/* ... up to --spacing-32: 8rem (128px) */
```

**Fluid Spacing (Responsive Scaling):**
```css
--space-xs: clamp(0.5rem, 0.4rem + 0.5vw, 0.75rem);      /* 8px → 12px */
--space-sm: clamp(0.75rem, 0.65rem + 0.5vw, 1rem);       /* 12px → 16px */
--space-md: clamp(1rem, 0.85rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);       /* 16px → 24px */
--space-lg: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);       /* 24px → 40px */
--space-xl: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2.5vw, 3.5rem);         /* 32px → 56px */
--space-2xl: clamp(3rem, 2.25rem + 3.75vw, 5rem);        /* 48px → 80px */
--space-3xl: clamp(4rem, 3rem + 5vw, 6.5rem);            /* 64px → 104px */
```

**Why clamp()?**
- Responsive without breakpoints
- Scales smoothly from min to max within viewport width
- Reduces need for media query rules

### Border Radius System (design-system.css:218-227)

```css
--radius-none: 0;
--radius-sm: 0.125rem;     /* 2px */
--radius-base: 0.25rem;    /* 4px */
--radius-md: 0.375rem;     /* 6px */
--radius-lg: 0.5rem;       /* 8px - default for inputs/buttons */
--radius-xl: 0.75rem;      /* 12px - default for cards */
--radius-2xl: 1rem;        /* 16px - modals */
--radius-3xl: 1.5rem;      /* 24px - hero sections */
--radius-full: 9999px;     /* Full circle/pill */
```

**Typography Scale (Fluid with clamp)** (design-system.css:312-325):
```css
--font-size-xs: clamp(0.75rem, 0.7rem + 0.25vw, 0.875rem);      /* 12px → 14px */
--font-size-sm: clamp(0.875rem, 0.8rem + 0.375vw, 1rem);        /* 14px → 16px */
--font-size-base: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.5vw, 1.125rem);        /* 16px → 18px */
--font-size-lg: clamp(1.125rem, 1rem + 0.625vw, 1.25rem);       /* 18px → 20px */
--font-size-xl: clamp(1.25rem, 1.1rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);        /* 20px → 24px */
--font-size-2xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.3rem + 1vw, 2rem);             /* 24px → 32px */
--font-size-3xl: clamp(1.875rem, 1.6rem + 1.375vw, 2.5rem);     /* 30px → 40px */
--font-size-4xl: clamp(2.25rem, 1.9rem + 1.75vw, 3rem);         /* 36px → 48px */
--font-size-5xl: clamp(3rem, 2.5rem + 2.5vw, 4rem);             /* 48px → 64px */
```

---

## 3. Animation & Transition System

### Durations (global.css:159-164)

```css
--transition-duration-fast: 200ms;          /* Button hovers, selections */
--transition-duration-base: 200ms;          /* Consistency with fast */
--transition-duration-medium: 300ms;        /* Standard transitions */
--transition-duration-slow: 500ms;          /* Page transitions */
--transition-duration-celebration: 2000ms;  /* Success celebrations */
```

**Synced with JavaScript:** `src/constants/animations.ts` mirrors these values for animations composable

### Easing Functions (global.css:166-174)

```css
--ease-linear: linear;
--ease-in: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1);           /* Accelerating */
--ease-out: cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1);          /* Most common, decelerating */
--ease-in-out: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);     /* Symmetrical */
--ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55);  /* Playful overshoot */
--ease-smooth: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);    /* Ultra-smooth, premium */
--ease-sharp: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);      /* Material design */
--ease-elastic: cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55); /* Springy */
```

### Predefined Keyframe Animations (global.css:177-217, design-system.css:432-527)

```css
/* Basic fade animations */
@keyframes fade-in {
  from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; }
}

@keyframes fade-out {
  from { opacity: 1; }
  to { opacity: 0; }
}

/* Directional slides */
@keyframes slide-in-up {
  from { transform: translateY(1rem); opacity: 0; }
  to { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 1; }
}

@keyframes slide-in-down {
  from { transform: translateY(-1rem); opacity: 0; }
  to { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 1; }
}

/* Scale animations */
@keyframes scale-in {
  from { transform: scale(0.9); opacity: 0; }
  to { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
}

@keyframes scale-out {
  from { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
  to { transform: scale(0.9); opacity: 0; }
}

/* Tailwind defaults */
@keyframes pulse {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
  50% { opacity: 0.5; }
}

@keyframes bounce {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(-25%); animation-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.8, 0, 1, 1); }
  50% { transform: none; animation-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1); }
}
```

**Utility Classes for Animations (design-system.css:531-569):**
```css
.animate-fade-in {
  animation: var(--animation-fade-in);
}

.animate-slide-in-up {
  animation: var(--animation-slide-in-up);
}

.transition-fast {
  transition: all var(--transition-fast);
}

.transition-medium {
  transition: all var(--transition-medium);
}
```

---

## 4. Dark Mode Implementation

### Dual Pattern Approach (design-system.css:164-178, 376-430)

**Method 1: Semantic color overrides**
```css
/* Light mode defaults in :root */
--color-surface-primary: #ffffff;
--color-surface-secondary: var(--color-gray-50);
--color-text-primary: var(--color-gray-900);

/* Dark mode overrides via [data-theme="dark"] */
[data-theme="dark"] {
  --color-surface-primary: var(--color-gray-800);
  --color-surface-secondary: var(--color-gray-900);
  --color-text-primary: var(--color-gray-100);
}
```

**Method 2: CSS custom variant (global.css:12)**
```css
@custom-variant dark (&:where([data-theme=dark], [data-theme=dark] *));
```

This enables Tailwind-like syntax:
```css
bg-white dark:bg-gray-800
text-gray-900 dark:text-white
```

**Dark Mode Gradient Overrides (design-system.css:405-430):**
```css
[data-theme="dark"] {
  --gradient-hero-base: linear-gradient(to bottom, #0f172a, #111827);

  /* Enhanced shadows for dark mode */
  --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.2);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4);

  /* Color adjustments */
  --gradient-accent-primary: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-500) 0%, var(--color-primary-600) 100%);
}
```

---

## 5. Gradient System

### Hero/Landing Gradients (design-system.css:256-268, global.css:403-519)

**Layered Radial Approach (5-layer system):**
```css
--gradient-hero-base: linear-gradient(to bottom, #ffffff, #f8fafc);
--gradient-hero-radial-1: radial-gradient(1100px 1100px at 8% 8%, rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.12), transparent 60%);
--gradient-hero-radial-2: radial-gradient(1200px 1200px at 92% 92%, rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.11), transparent 60%);
--gradient-hero-radial-3: radial-gradient(1300px 900px at -10% 50%, rgba(45, 212, 191, 0.08), transparent 65%);
--gradient-hero-radial-4: radial-gradient(1300px 900px at 110% 45%, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08), transparent 65%);
--gradient-hero-radial-5: radial-gradient(900px 900px at 95% 10%, rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06), transparent 65%);

.bg-gradient-hero {
  background:
    var(--gradient-hero-radial-1),
    var(--gradient-hero-radial-2),
    var(--gradient-hero-radial-3),
    var(--gradient-hero-radial-4),
    var(--gradient-hero-radial-5),
    var(--gradient-hero-base);
}
```

**Why 5 layers?**
- Creates depth without single-point focus
- Different color hues at different positions (indigo, purple, cyan, blue, pink)
- Overlapping ellipses create organic, non-artificial appearance
- Transparency decreases slightly for each layer adds dimensional depth

**Gradient Variants:**
```css
--gradient-hero-vibrant: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-100) 0%, var(--color-primary-200) 100%);
--gradient-hero-subtle: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-gray-50) 0%, var(--color-surface-primary) 100%);

/* Accent gradients */
--gradient-accent-primary: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-400) 0%, var(--color-primary-600) 100%);
--gradient-accent-purple: linear-gradient(135deg, #c084fc 0%, #7c3aed 100%);
--gradient-accent-warm: linear-gradient(135deg, #fb923c 0%, #f59e0b 100%);

/* Feature section */
--gradient-feature-light: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-primary-50), var(--color-gray-50));
--gradient-feature-card: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-surface-primary), var(--color-surface-secondary));

/* CTA with glow effect */
--gradient-cta: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-500) 0%, var(--color-primary-600) 100%);
--gradient-cta-hover: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-600) 0%, var(--color-primary-700) 100%);

.bg-gradient-cta {
  background: var(--gradient-cta);
  box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 124, 137, 0.3);
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.bg-gradient-cta:hover {
  background: var(--gradient-cta-hover);
  box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(0, 124, 137, 0.5);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}
```

**Mesh Gradients (Complex overlapping):**
```css
--gradient-mesh:
  radial-gradient(at 20% 30%, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.12) 0px, transparent 50%),
  radial-gradient(at 80% 70%, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.12) 0px, transparent 50%),
  radial-gradient(at 40% 80%, rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.10) 0px, transparent 50%),
  linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-surface-primary), var(--color-surface-secondary));

.bg-gradient-mesh-overlay::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: var(--gradient-mesh-overlay);
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: 1;
}
```

**Text Gradients:**
```css
.text-gradient-primary {
  background: var(--gradient-accent-primary);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  color: transparent; /* Fallback */
}
```

**Animated Gradients:**
```css
@keyframes gradientShift {
  0%, 100% {
    background-position: 0% 50%;
  }
  50% {
    background-position: 100% 50%;
  }
}

.bg-gradient-animated {
  background-size: 200% 200%;
  animation: gradientShift 8s ease infinite;
}
```

---

## 6. Glass Morphism & Depth System

### Glass Effects (utilities.css:21-290)

**Three Main Variants with Dark Mode:**

```css
.glass-subtle {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
}

[data-theme="dark"] .glass-subtle {
  background: rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.8);
  border: 1px solid rgba(55, 65, 81, 0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

.glass-medium {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.glass-strong {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
  backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
  box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
}
```

**Component-Specific Glass:**
```css
.glass-card {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
  backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
  border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  padding: var(--spacing-6);
}

.glass-navbar {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(180%);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
}

.glass-modal {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
  backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
  border-radius: var(--radius-2xl);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-2xl);
}
```

**Accessibility Respects (utilities.css:35-64):**
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .glass-subtle {
    backdrop-filter: none;
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: none;
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-transparency: reduce) {
  .glass-subtle {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
    backdrop-filter: none;
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: none;
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-data: reduce) {
  .glass-subtle {
    backdrop-filter: none;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.98);
  }
}
```

### Modern Depth System (utilities.css:502-840)

**Layered Shadow System (Ambient + Contact):**

```css
.shadow-depth-1 {
  box-shadow:
    0px 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06),    /* contact shadow - close */
    0px 0px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);    /* ambient shadow - diffuse */
}

.shadow-depth-2 {
  box-shadow:
    0px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08),
    0px 0px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.shadow-depth-4, .shadow-depth-6, .shadow-depth-8,
.shadow-depth-12, .shadow-depth-16, .shadow-depth-24 {
  /* Progressive scaling of contact + ambient shadows */
}

/* Dark mode shadows 3-4x stronger for visibility */
[data-theme="dark"] .shadow-depth-1 {
  box-shadow:
    0px 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.30),
    0px 0px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.40);
}
```

**Color-Matched Shadows (Using OKLCH):**
```css
.shadow-primary {
  box-shadow:
    0px 4px 12px oklch(50% 0.16 200 / 0.15),    /* Primary color shadow */
    0px 0px 4px oklch(50% 0.16 200 / 0.10);
}

.shadow-success {
  box-shadow:
    0px 4px 12px oklch(65% 0.17 160 / 0.15),    /* Green shadow */
    0px 0px 4px oklch(65% 0.17 160 / 0.10);
}

.shadow-error {
  box-shadow:
    0px 4px 12px oklch(62% 0.22 25 / 0.15),     /* Red shadow */
    0px 0px 4px oklch(62% 0.22 25 / 0.10);
}
```

**Neumorphism Effects:**
```css
.neomorph-flat {
  background: var(--color-surface-primary);
  box-shadow:
    8px 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12),      /* Drop shadow */
    -8px -8px 16px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.70);  /* Highlight */
  border-radius: var(--radius-2xl);
}

.neomorph-pressed {
  box-shadow:
    inset 4px 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12),
    inset -4px -4px 8px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.70);
}

.neomorph-raised {
  box-shadow:
    12px 12px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14),
    -12px -12px 24px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.80);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}
```

**Advanced Glass Effects (Glassmorphism 2.0):**
```css
.glass-vibrant {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.70);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(180%);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  box-shadow:
    0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08),
    inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);    /* Inset highlight */
}

.glass-frosted {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.50);
  backdrop-filter: blur(32px) saturate(200%);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
  box-shadow:
    0 12px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10),
    inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
}
```

**Elevation Semantic Utilities:**
```css
.elevation-surface { box-shadow: none; z-index: 0; }
.elevation-raised { box-shadow: 0px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08); z-index: 1; }
.elevation-overlay { box-shadow: 0px 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10); z-index: 10; }
.elevation-floating { box-shadow: 0px 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14); z-index: 50; }
.elevation-modal { box-shadow: 0px 16px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18); z-index: var(--z-index-modal); }
```

**Depth Layering:**
```css
.layer-back {
  z-index: 1;
  transform: translateY(8px);
  opacity: 0.90;
  filter: blur(0.5px);
}

.layer-middle {
  z-index: 2;
  transform: translateY(4px);
  opacity: 0.95;
}

.layer-front {
  z-index: 3;
  transform: translateY(0px);
}

/* Depth through scale and contrast */
.depth-recede {
  opacity: 0.80;
  filter: brightness(0.95) saturate(0.90);
  transform: scale(0.98);
}

.depth-advance {
  opacity: 1;
  filter: brightness(1.05) saturate(1.10);
  transform: scale(1.02);
}

.depth-transition {
  transition:
    transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1),
    box-shadow 300ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1),
    opacity 300ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1),
    filter 300ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

.depth-transition:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px) scale(1.02);
}
```

---

## 7. Focus & Accessibility System

### Focus Ring Utilities (utilities.css:296-407)

**Primary Focus Ring:**
```css
.focus-ring:focus,
.focus-ring:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-primary-500);
}

@media (prefers-contrast: high) {
  .focus-ring:focus,
  .focus-ring:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-primary-600);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
}
```

**Semantic Focus Rings:**
```css
.focus-ring-error:focus-visible { box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus-error); }
.focus-ring-success:focus-visible { box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus-success); }
.focus-ring-info:focus-visible { box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1); }
.focus-ring-warning:focus-visible { box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1); }

.focus-ring-offset:focus-visible {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus-primary), 0 0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
}

.focus-ring-inset:focus-visible {
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 2px var(--color-primary-500);
}
```

