## 15. Responsive Design Patterns

### Fluid Scaling with clamp() (Throughout)

Instead of media queries for sizing:
```css
/* Typography scales smoothly from 48px to 72px */
--font-size-display-2xl: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);

/* Spacing scales from 24px to 40px */
--space-lg: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
```

**Why clamp()?**
1. **Minimum value** - smallest acceptable size (guarantees legibility on tiny screens)
2. **Preferred value** - viewport-relative scaling (smooth responsiveness)
3. **Maximum value** - largest acceptable size (prevents huge text on ultra-wide screens)

### Mobile Breakpoints (design-system.css:1063-1179)

```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  /* Extra small mobile phones */
  .responsive-mobile-xs { font-size: 14px; }
  .btn-base { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); }
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  /* Small mobile devices */
  .glass-medium, .glass-strong {
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px) !important;  /* Reduce blur on mobile */
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  /* Mobile optimizations */
  .form-control-base { font-size: 16px; }  /* Prevents iOS zoom */
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  /* Desktop enhancements */
  .body-hero { font-size: 1.5rem; }
}
```

