## 2. Design Token System

### Color Palette Architecture (design-system.css:9-143)

**OKLCH with RGB Fallbacks Pattern:**

```css
:root {
  /* Primary Brand Colors - OKLCH with RGB fallbacks for Safari < 15.4 */
  --color-primary-50: #e6f3f4;                    /* RGB fallback */
  --color-primary-50: oklch(95% 0.03 200);        /* Modern OKLCH */
  --color-primary-100: #cce5e7;
  --color-primary-100: oklch(90% 0.05 200);
  /* ... continues for 50-950 scale */
  --color-primary-500: #007c89;  /* Base teal - brand color */
  --color-primary-500: oklch(50% 0.16 200);
}
```

**Why OKLCH?**
- Perceptually uniform color scales (uniform lightness across all hues)
- Better interpolation between colors
- Modern color space for progressive enhancement
- Safari fallback ensures cross-browser compatibility

**Color Scales:** Each semantic color (primary, success, warning, error, info) has 11 shades (50-950)

**Semantic Color System:**
```css
--color-primary-*      /* Teal #007c89 - Brand color */
--color-success-*      /* Green #10b981 - Positive states */
--color-warning-*      /* Amber #f59e0b - Cautionary states */
--color-error-*        /* Red #ef4444 - Destructive states */
--color-info-*         /* Blue #3b82f6 - Informational states */
--color-gray-*         /* Neutral grays */

/* Surface colors - Adapt with dark mode */
--color-surface-primary        /* #ffffff light, gray-800 dark */
--color-surface-secondary      /* gray-50 light, gray-900 dark */
--color-surface-tertiary       /* gray-100 light, gray-950 dark */
--color-surface-inverse        /* gray-900 light, #ffffff dark */

/* Text colors - Hierarchy system */
--color-text-primary           /* gray-900 light, gray-100 dark */
--color-text-secondary         /* gray-600 light, gray-300 dark */
--color-text-tertiary          /* gray-500 light, gray-400 dark */
--color-text-placeholder       /* gray-400 light, gray-500 dark */
```

### Spacing System (design-system.css:179-217)

**Fixed Spacing Scale (4px base unit):**
```css
--spacing-0: 0;
--spacing-px: 1px;
--spacing-0_5: 0.125rem;   /* 2px */
--spacing-1: 0.25rem;      /* 4px */
--spacing-2: 0.5rem;       /* 8px */
--spacing-3: 0.75rem;      /* 12px */
--spacing-4: 1rem;         /* 16px base */
--spacing-6: 1.5rem;       /* 24px */
--spacing-8: 2rem;         /* 32px */
/* ... up to --spacing-32: 8rem (128px) */
```

**Fluid Spacing (Responsive Scaling):**
```css
--space-xs: clamp(0.5rem, 0.4rem + 0.5vw, 0.75rem);      /* 8px → 12px */
--space-sm: clamp(0.75rem, 0.65rem + 0.5vw, 1rem);       /* 12px → 16px */
--space-md: clamp(1rem, 0.85rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);       /* 16px → 24px */
--space-lg: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);       /* 24px → 40px */
--space-xl: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2.5vw, 3.5rem);         /* 32px → 56px */
--space-2xl: clamp(3rem, 2.25rem + 3.75vw, 5rem);        /* 48px → 80px */
--space-3xl: clamp(4rem, 3rem + 5vw, 6.5rem);            /* 64px → 104px */
```

**Why clamp()?**
- Responsive without breakpoints
- Scales smoothly from min to max within viewport width
- Reduces need for media query rules

### Border Radius System (design-system.css:218-227)

```css
--radius-none: 0;
