## 1. CSS Architecture & Layering System

### Cascade Layer Organization (global.css:4)

```css
@layer reset, theme, composition, utilities, components, overrides;

@import "./design-system.css" layer(theme);
@import "./typography.css" layer(components);
@import "./utilities.css" layer(utilities);
```

**Why this matters:**
- Explicit layer ordering prevents CSS cascade conflicts
- `theme` layer (design-system.css) sets base tokens
- `components` layer (typography.css) defines component base styles
- `utilities` layer (utilities.css) provides high-level patterns
- Each layer has predictable specificity

**Design Decision:** Tailwind v4 CSS-first approach eliminates bloated config files. All customization flows through CSS custom properties.

