# Vue Component Architecture Analysis - Socialaize

## Executive Summary

The Socialaize Vue component system demonstrates a highly organized, modular approach to building maintainable UI. Based on analysis of `/src/components/vue/base/`, `/buttons/`, `/cards/`, and `/inputs/`, the codebase follows consistent patterns for composition, styling, accessibility, and dark mode support.

---

## 1. COMPONENT COMPOSITION PATTERNS

### 1.1 Base Component Structure

**File Structure:**
```
src/components/vue/
├── base/
│   ├── Button.vue          (Polymorphic, highly configurable)
│   ├── Badge.vue           (Semantic, interactive variants)
│   ├── Card.vue            (Container with slots)
│   └── index.ts            (Exports + type definitions)
├── buttons/
│   ├── PrimaryButton.vue   (Semantic wrapper)
│   ├── OutlineButton.vue   (Specialized variant)
│   ├── MenuButton.vue      (Domain-specific)
│   └── providers/          (Social login buttons)
├── inputs/
│   ├── TextInput.vue       (Form field with validation)
│   ├── SelectDropdown.vue  (Advanced with floating UI)
│   └── others...
└── cards/
    ├── WorkflowCard.vue    (Complex, interactive)
    ├── PricingCard.vue     (Specialized content)
    └── others...
```

### 1.2 Script Setup Pattern

**All components use `<script setup lang="ts">`:**
- Composition API with TypeScript
- Explicit prop definitions with `defineProps<Props>()`
- Default values via `withDefaults()`
- Typed emits via `defineEmits<{ ... }>()`

**Button.vue Example:**
```typescript
interface Props {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "outline" | "ghost" | "danger" | "success" | "warning";
  size?: "xs" | "sm" | "md" | "lg" | "xl";
  text?: string;
  icon?: string;
  iconPosition?: "left" | "right";
  loading?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  as?: "button" | "a" | "router-link";
  type?: "button" | "submit" | "reset";
  href?: string;
  to?: string | object;
  class?: string;
  iconClass?: string;
  textClass?: string;
}

const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  variant: "primary",
  size: "md",
  iconPosition: "left",
  as: "button",
  type: "button",
});
```

---

## 2. TAILWIND UTILITIES ORGANIZATION

### 2.1 Class Organization Pattern

**Components use consistent class ordering:**
1. Layout/Display utilities (flex, grid, etc.)
2. Sizing utilities (w-, h-, p-, m-, etc.)
3. Typography utilities (font-, text-, etc.)
4. Color utilities (bg-, text-, border-, etc.)
5. Interactive utilities (hover:, active:, etc.)
6. Responsive utilities (sm:, md:, lg:, etc.)
7. Conditional classes (passed props)

**Example from Button.vue:**
```vue
:class="[
  'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg font-medium transition-all duration-fast border',
  sizeClass,        // sizing from computed
  variantClass,     // colors from computed
  {
    'opacity-60 pointer-events-none cursor-not-allowed transform-none': disabled || loading,
    'cursor-pointer transform hover:scale-[1.02] active:scale-[0.98]': !disabled && !loading,
  },
  props.class,      // pass-through custom classes
]"
```

### 2.2 Computed Class Maps

**Pattern: Centralized variant/size mappings in computed properties**

```typescript
const sizeClass = computed(() => {
  const sizeMap = {
    xs: "px-2 py-1 text-xs gap-1",
    sm: "px-3 py-2 text-sm gap-2",
    md: "px-4 py-2 text-base gap-2",
    lg: "px-6 py-3 text-lg gap-3",
    xl: "px-8 py-4 text-xl gap-3",
  };
  return sizeMap[props.size];
});

const variantClass = computed(() => {
  const variantMap = {
    primary: "bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600 active:bg-primary-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    secondary: "bg-gray-500 hover:bg-gray-600 active:bg-gray-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    outline: "border-2 border-primary-500 text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-500 hover:text-white dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:text-white bg-transparent shadow-sm hover:shadow-md focus-ring",
    ghost: "text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-50 active:bg-primary-100 dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:bg-primary-950 dark:active:bg-primary-900 border-transparent focus-ring",
    danger: "bg-error-500 hover:bg-error-600 active:bg-error-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    success: "bg-success-500 hover:bg-success-600 active:bg-success-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    warning: "bg-warning-500 hover:bg-warning-600 active:bg-warning-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
  };
  return variantMap[props.variant];
});
```

### 2.3 Design System Token Usage

**From `src/styles/global.css` @theme layer:**
```css
--color-primary-50 through 950
--color-success-50 through 950
--color-warning-50 through 950
--color-error-50 through 950
--color-info-50 through 950
--spacing-0 through 32
--radius-none, sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl, full
--shadow-sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl
--transition-fast (150ms), base (200ms), medium (300ms), slow (500ms)
--ease-out, ease-in-out
```

**Applied in components:**
```vue
transition-all duration-fast        <!-- Uses Tailwind's duration- + design tokens -->
rounded-lg                          <!-- Uses --radius-lg -->
shadow-md hover:shadow-lg           <!-- Uses --shadow-md -->
gap-2 px-4 py-2                     <!-- Uses --spacing values -->
```

---

## 3. STYLING CONVENTIONS

### 3.1 Dark Mode Implementation

**System uses data-theme attribute:**
```css
@custom-variant dark (&:where([data-theme=dark], [data-theme=dark] *));
```

**Applied consistently in all components:**
```vue
<!-- In dark: mode prefix (Vue)  -->
dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700

<!-- From base/Button.vue -->
outline: "border-2 border-primary-500 text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-500 hover:text-white dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:text-white bg-transparent shadow-sm hover:shadow-md focus-ring",

ghost: "text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-50 active:bg-primary-100 dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:bg-primary-950 dark:active:bg-primary-900 border-transparent focus-ring",
```

### 3.2 Focus Ring Utilities

**Design system provides semantic focus classes:**
```css
.focus-ring:focus,
.focus-ring:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-primary-500);
}

.focus-ring-error:focus,
.focus-ring-error:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus-error);
  border-color: var(--color-error-500);
}
```

**Components use in class strings:**
```typescript
primary: "...text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
outline: "...text-primary-600 ...focus-ring",
danger: "...text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
```

### 3.3 Glass Morphism Effects

**Five built-in glass variants from utilities.css:**
```css
.glass-subtle     /* blur(8px), subtle backdrop */
.glass-medium     /* blur(12px), balanced */
.glass-strong     /* blur(16px), premium feel */
.glass-card       /* blur(10px), card-specific */
.glass-navbar     /* blur(20px) + saturate(180%) */
.glass-modal      /* blur(16px), modal overlay */
```

**Used in components:**
```vue
<!-- From Card.vue -->
:class="{
  'glass-subtle': glass === 'subtle',
  'glass-medium': glass === 'medium',
  'glass-strong': glass === 'strong',
}"

<!-- From PricingSection.vue -->
<div class="glass-medium rounded-2xl p-8">
<div class="glass-card h-full transform hover:scale-[1.02]">
```

### 3.4 Responsive Patterns

**Tailwind breakpoint prefixes used throughout:**
```vue
<!-- Responsive padding from WorkflowCard -->
class="p-4 sm:p-5 lg:p-6"

<!-- Responsive text sizing -->
text-[0.9375rem] md:text-base

<!-- Responsive layout -->
lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8

<!-- Mobile optimizations -->
sm:flex-row sm:justify-between
```

### 3.5 Transition/Animation Utilities

**Consistent animation patterns:**
```typescript
// From base/Button.vue - scale transform on interaction
'cursor-pointer transform hover:scale-[1.02] active:scale-[0.98]': !disabled && !loading

// From Badge.vue - interactive feedback
'cursor-pointer hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-fast': interactive

// Spinner animation
const spinnerClass = computed(() => {
  return `border-2 border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin ${sizeMap[props.size]} ${colorMap[props.variant]}`;
});
```

**Duration tokens from design system:**
- `duration-fast` (150ms / --transition-fast)
- `duration-base` (200ms / --transition-base)  
- `duration-300` (300ms / --transition-medium)
- `duration-500` (500ms / --transition-slow)

---

## 4. PROPS AND VARIANTS IMPLEMENTATION

### 4.1 Button Variants System

**7 built-in variants (primary, secondary, outline, ghost, danger, success, warning)**

```typescript
variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "outline" | "ghost" | "danger" | "success" | "warning";

const variantClass = computed(() => {
  const variantMap = {
    primary: "bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600 active:bg-primary-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    secondary: "bg-gray-500 hover:bg-gray-600 active:bg-gray-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    outline: "border-2 border-primary-500 text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-500 hover:text-white dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:text-white bg-transparent shadow-sm hover:shadow-md focus-ring",
    ghost: "text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-50 active:bg-primary-100 dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:bg-primary-950 dark:active:bg-primary-900 border-transparent focus-ring",
    danger: "bg-error-500 hover:bg-error-600 active:bg-error-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    success: "bg-success-500 hover:bg-success-600 active:bg-success-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    warning: "bg-warning-500 hover:bg-warning-600 active:bg-warning-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
  };
  return variantMap[props.variant];
});
```

### 4.2 Size System (5 sizes)

```typescript
size?: "xs" | "sm" | "md" | "lg" | "xl";

const sizeClass = computed(() => {
  const sizeMap = {
    xs: "px-2 py-1 text-xs gap-1",
    sm: "px-3 py-2 text-sm gap-2",
    md: "px-4 py-2 text-base gap-2",
    lg: "px-6 py-3 text-lg gap-3",
    xl: "px-8 py-4 text-xl gap-3",
  };
  return sizeMap[props.size];
});
```

### 4.3 Polymorphic `as` Prop

**Buttons support rendering as button, link, or router-link:**

```typescript
as?: "button" | "a" | "router-link";

<component
  :is="as"
  :disabled="disabled || loading"
  :href="as === 'a' ? href : undefined"
  :to="as === 'router-link' ? to : undefined"
  :type="as === 'button' ? type : undefined"
/>
```

### 4.4 Badge Variants (7 variants)

```typescript
variant?: "default" | "primary" | "secondary" | "success" | "warning" | "error" | "info";

const variantClass = computed(() => {
  const variantMap = {
    default: "bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200",
    primary: "bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 dark:bg-primary-900 dark:text-primary-200",
    secondary: "bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200",
    success: "bg-success-100 text-success-800 dark:bg-success-900 dark:text-success-200",
    warning: "bg-warning-100 text-warning-800 dark:bg-warning-900 dark:text-warning-200",
    error: "bg-error-100 text-error-800 dark:bg-error-900 dark:text-error-200",
    info: "bg-info-100 text-info-800 dark:bg-info-900 dark:text-info-200",
  };
  return variantMap[props.variant];
});
```

### 4.5 Card Props System

```typescript
interface Props {
  title?: string;
  icon?: string;
  variant?: "default" | "primary" | "success" | "warning" | "error";
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  padding?: "none" | "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  interactive?: boolean;
  glass?: "none" | "subtle" | "medium" | "strong";
  class?: string;
  titleClass?: string;
  contentClass?: string;
  iconClass?: string;
}
```

---

## 5. ANIMATION INTEGRATION PATTERNS

### 5.1 Animation Composables Usage

**Components use VueUse for animations:**
```typescript
// From WorkflowCard.vue
import { useIntersectionObserver, useMutationObserver, usePreferredReducedMotion, useMediaQuery, useDebounceFn } from '@vueuse/core'

const prefersReducedMotion = usePreferredReducedMotion()
const isMobile = useMediaQuery('(max-width: 768px)')
```

### 5.2 Conditional Animation Based on Preferences

```typescript
// From WorkflowCard.vue
if (!prefersReducedMotion.value) {
  baseClasses.push('will-change-transform', 'gpu-acceleration')
}

// Apply animations conditionally
:class="[
  prefersReducedMotion ? 'transition-none' : 'transition-fast',
  prefersReducedMotion ? '' : 'animate-fade-in'
]"
```

### 5.3 Tailwind Animation Classes

```css
animate-fade-in       /* Opacity + translateY animation */
animate-spin          /* Rotation for loaders */
animate-pulse         /* Opacity pulsing for skeletons */
animate-slide-in-down /* Dropdown entrance */
animate-float         /* Floating decoration elements */
```

### 5.4 Scoped Animations in Components

**PricingSection.vue example:**
```css
@keyframes float {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-20px); }
}

@keyframes float-slow {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0) rotate(12deg); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-15px) rotate(12deg); }
}

.animate-float { animation: float 8s ease-in-out infinite; will-change: transform; }
.animate-float-slow { animation: float-slow 12s ease-in-out infinite; will-change: transform; }
```

---

## 6. DARK MODE HANDLING

### 6.1 Systematic Dark Mode Approach

**Every color in every component has a dark: counterpart:**

```vue
<!-- From TextInput.vue -->
:class="[
  'w-full py-3 px-4 h-12 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg',
  'bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-white',
  'transition-all duration-base focus-ring focus:border-primary-500',
  'disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:bg-gray-100 dark:disabled:bg-gray-700',
]"
```

### 6.2 Design System Dark Mode Support

**From utilities.css - Complete dark variants:**
```css
[data-theme="dark"] .glass-subtle {
  background: rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.8);
  border: 1px solid rgba(55, 65, 81, 0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

[data-theme="dark"] .glass-medium {
  background: rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.9);
  border: 1px solid rgba(55, 65, 81, 0.4);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}
```

### 6.3 Media Query Fallbacks for Dark Mode

```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  /* Enhanced shadows for dark mode visibility */
  .shadow-md {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md, 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4), 0 2px 4px -2px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4));
  }

  /* Improved text contrast in dark mode */
  .text-primary-dark {
    color: rgb(243, 244, 246);
    text-shadow: 0 0 0.5px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }
}
```

---

## 7. SLOT USAGE AND COMPONENT FLEXIBILITY

### 7.1 Named Slots Pattern

**Card.vue demonstrates slot architecture:**
```vue
<header v-if="title || $slots.header">
  <div v-if="title">Header content</div>
  <slot name="header" />
</header>

<div :class="contentClass">
  <slot />
</div>

<footer v-if="$slots.footer">
  <slot name="footer" />
</footer>
```

**Usage:**
```vue
<Card title="Title">
  <template #header>Custom header</template>
  <p>Content</p>
  <template #footer>Actions</template>
</Card>
```

### 7.2 Default Slot Content

```vue
<!-- From Button.vue -->
<span v-if="text || $slots.default">
  <slot>{{ text }}</slot>
</span>

<!-- Usage either way -->
<Button text="Click me" />
<Button><span>Click me</span></Button>
```

### 7.3 Slot Visibility Detection

**Smart rendering based on slot presence:**
```vue
<header v-if="title || $slots.header" class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
  <!-- Only renders if title prop OR header slot is provided -->
</header>

<footer v-if="$slots.footer" class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t">
  <!-- Only renders footer if slot is provided -->
</footer>
```

---

## 8. ACCESSIBILITY PATTERNS

### 8.1 ARIA Labels and Descriptions

**From WorkflowCard.vue (1800+ lines):**
```vue
:aria-label="`Workflow: ${workflow.name || 'Untitled Workflow'}`"
:aria-describedby="`workflow-status-${workflow.$id} workflow-description-${workflow.$id}`"
:aria-live="isUpdating ? 'polite' : undefined"
:aria-invalid="!editData.name.trim()"
:aria-expanded="showFullDescription"
```

### 8.2 Semantic HTML

```vue
<!-- Proper semantic elements -->
<article role="article">
  <header role="banner">
  <section role="region" aria-label="Workflow details">
  <footer role="contentinfo">
  <div role="status" aria-live="polite">
  <div role="form" aria-label="Edit workflow form">
```

### 8.3 Focus Management

```typescript
// From WorkflowCard.vue
const startEditing = async () => {
  resetEditData();
  isEditing.value = true;

  if (import.meta.client) {
    await nextTick();
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      nameInputRef.value?.focus();  // Focus on edit start
    });
  }
};

const cancelEditing = () => {
  // Return focus to card after cancel
  if (import.meta.client) {
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      cardRef.value?.focus();
    });
  }
};
```

### 8.4 Keyboard Navigation

```typescript
const handleCardKeydown = (event: KeyboardEvent) => {
  if (isEditing.value || event.target !== event.currentTarget) return;

  switch (event.key) {
    case 'Enter':
    case ' ':
      event.preventDefault();
      emit('open-editor', props.workflow.$id);
      break;
    case 'Delete':
    case 'Backspace':
      if (event.shiftKey) handleDeleteClick();
      break;
    case 't':
    case 'T':
      if (!event.ctrlKey && !event.metaKey) {
        event.preventDefault();
        handleToggleActive(!props.workflow.isActive);
      }
      break;
  }
};
```

### 8.5 Form Validation States

**From TextInput.vue:**
```typescript
const inputClass = computed(() => {
  if (!mounted.value) return "";
  if (!hasBlurredInput.value) return "";
  if (props.isValidTest) {
    return props.isValidTest(modelValue.value) || props.isValid
      ? "success !border-success-500 focus:!shadow-focus-success"
      : "error !border-error-500 focus:!shadow-focus-error";
  }
});
```

---

## 9. SSR SAFETY PATTERNS

### 9.1 Client-Only Rendering

```typescript
// From TextInput.vue
import { useMounted } from "@vueuse/core";

const mounted = useMounted();

const inputClass = computed(() => {
  if (!mounted.value) return "";  // Avoid rendering before mount
  // Validation logic...
});

// In template
<Icon v-if="icon && mounted" :icon="icon" />
```

### 9.2 Import.meta.client Guards

```typescript
// From WorkflowCard.vue
if (import.meta.client) {
  const { stop } = useIntersectionObserver(/* ... */);
  onUnmounted(() => stop());
}

// And for performance monitoring
if (import.meta.env.DEV && import.meta.client) {
  onMounted(() => {
    const observer = new PerformanceObserver(/* ... */);
  });
}
```

---

## 10. MODULAR EXPORTS PATTERN

### 10.1 Centralized Base Component Exports

**From base/index.ts:**
```typescript
export { default as Card } from './Card.vue';
export { default as Button } from './Button.vue';
export { default as Badge } from './Badge.vue';
export { default as BaseModal } from '../modals/BaseModal.vue';
export { default as TextInput } from '../inputs/TextInput.vue';
export { default as SelectDropdown } from '../inputs/SelectDropdown.vue';
export { default as PrimaryButton } from '../buttons/PrimaryButton.vue';
export { default as OutlineButton } from '../buttons/OutlineButton.vue';

// Type exports for better IDE support
export interface CardProps { ... }
export interface ButtonProps { ... }
export interface BadgeProps { ... }

// Design system utilities
export const designTokens = { ... };
export const componentSizes = { ... };
export const getVariantClasses = (variant, type) => { ... };
```

---

## 11. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PRINCIPLES

### Pattern Summary:

1. **Composition over Configuration** - Use `<script setup>` exclusively
2. **Prop-Driven Styling** - All styles computed from props
3. **Variant Maps** - Centralized variant/size definitions as computed properties
4. **Dark Mode-First** - Every color has `dark:` counterpart
5. **Glass Morphism** - Consistent utility classes for effects
6. **Accessibility-First** - ARIA attributes, semantic HTML, focus management
7. **Motion-Respecting** - Conditional animations based on `prefers-reduced-motion`
8. **Slot Flexibility** - Named slots for maximum composability
9. **Type Safety** - Strict TypeScript interfaces for all props
10. **Performance-Conscious** - `useMounted()`, lazy visibility detection, GPU acceleration classes
11. **Responsive by Default** - Tailwind breakpoint prefixes throughout
12. **Design Token Integration** - CSS custom properties for all values

