# Vue Component Architecture Analysis - Socialaize

## Executive Summary

The Socialaize Vue component system demonstrates a highly organized, modular approach to building maintainable UI. Based on analysis of `/src/components/vue/base/`, `/buttons/`, `/cards/`, and `/inputs/`, the codebase follows consistent patterns for composition, styling, accessibility, and dark mode support.

---

## 1. COMPONENT COMPOSITION PATTERNS

### 1.1 Base Component Structure

**File Structure:**
```
src/components/vue/
├── base/
│   ├── Button.vue          (Polymorphic, highly configurable)
│   ├── Badge.vue           (Semantic, interactive variants)
│   ├── Card.vue            (Container with slots)
│   └── index.ts            (Exports + type definitions)
├── buttons/
│   ├── PrimaryButton.vue   (Semantic wrapper)
│   ├── OutlineButton.vue   (Specialized variant)
│   ├── MenuButton.vue      (Domain-specific)
│   └── providers/          (Social login buttons)
├── inputs/
│   ├── TextInput.vue       (Form field with validation)
│   ├── SelectDropdown.vue  (Advanced with floating UI)
│   └── others...
└── cards/
    ├── WorkflowCard.vue    (Complex, interactive)
    ├── PricingCard.vue     (Specialized content)
    └── others...
```

### 1.2 Script Setup Pattern

**All components use `<script setup lang="ts">`:**
- Composition API with TypeScript
- Explicit prop definitions with `defineProps<Props>()`
- Default values via `withDefaults()`
- Typed emits via `defineEmits<{ ... }>()`

**Button.vue Example:**
```typescript
interface Props {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "outline" | "ghost" | "danger" | "success" | "warning";
  size?: "xs" | "sm" | "md" | "lg" | "xl";
  text?: string;
  icon?: string;
  iconPosition?: "left" | "right";
  loading?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  as?: "button" | "a" | "router-link";
  type?: "button" | "submit" | "reset";
  href?: string;
  to?: string | object;
  class?: string;
  iconClass?: string;
  textClass?: string;
}

const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  variant: "primary",
  size: "md",
  iconPosition: "left",
  as: "button",
  type: "button",
});
```

---

## 2. TAILWIND UTILITIES ORGANIZATION

### 2.1 Class Organization Pattern

**Components use consistent class ordering:**
1. Layout/Display utilities (flex, grid, etc.)
2. Sizing utilities (w-, h-, p-, m-, etc.)
3. Typography utilities (font-, text-, etc.)
4. Color utilities (bg-, text-, border-, etc.)
5. Interactive utilities (hover:, active:, etc.)
6. Responsive utilities (sm:, md:, lg:, etc.)
7. Conditional classes (passed props)

**Example from Button.vue:**
```vue
:class="[
  'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg font-medium transition-all duration-fast border',
  sizeClass,        // sizing from computed
  variantClass,     // colors from computed
  {
    'opacity-60 pointer-events-none cursor-not-allowed transform-none': disabled || loading,
    'cursor-pointer transform hover:scale-[1.02] active:scale-[0.98]': !disabled && !loading,
  },
  props.class,      // pass-through custom classes
]"
```

### 2.2 Computed Class Maps

**Pattern: Centralized variant/size mappings in computed properties**

```typescript
const sizeClass = computed(() => {
  const sizeMap = {
    xs: "px-2 py-1 text-xs gap-1",
    sm: "px-3 py-2 text-sm gap-2",
    md: "px-4 py-2 text-base gap-2",
    lg: "px-6 py-3 text-lg gap-3",
    xl: "px-8 py-4 text-xl gap-3",
  };
  return sizeMap[props.size];
});

const variantClass = computed(() => {
  const variantMap = {
    primary: "bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600 active:bg-primary-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    secondary: "bg-gray-500 hover:bg-gray-600 active:bg-gray-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    outline: "border-2 border-primary-500 text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-500 hover:text-white dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:text-white bg-transparent shadow-sm hover:shadow-md focus-ring",
    ghost: "text-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-50 active:bg-primary-100 dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:bg-primary-950 dark:active:bg-primary-900 border-transparent focus-ring",
    danger: "bg-error-500 hover:bg-error-600 active:bg-error-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    success: "bg-success-500 hover:bg-success-600 active:bg-success-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
    warning: "bg-warning-500 hover:bg-warning-600 active:bg-warning-700 text-white border-transparent shadow-md hover:shadow-lg focus-ring",
  };
  return variantMap[props.variant];
});
```

### 2.3 Design System Token Usage

**From `src/styles/global.css` @theme layer:**
```css
